
[1]wealth

   WEALTH, n.

   1. Prosperity; external happiness.

   2. Riches; large possessions of money, goods or land; that abundance of
   worldly estate which exceeds the estate of the greater part of the
   community; affluence; opulence.

   Each day new wealth without their care provides.
